<br>
Umm, I didn't say anything about that (if that is even directed at me).  <br>
<br>
The main reason why I mentioned aggro is, that is all I have ever heard being complained about by warriors who come to the SK boards.  They complain that we are selected to tank in exp groups over them because of our aggro abilities.  <br>
<br>
As for the HP and AC thing, well....maybe the Paladin and SK in question had more DKP than the warriors?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     I really don't know but if all the defensive AA's are the same and the gear is the same the warrior will have more HPs everytime.  Warriors innately have more HPs so I would think there would have to be a severe discrepency in AA's or gear for a Paladin to have more HPs.  AC would have to be gear related as well so not an argument there either really.<br>
<br>
I fully understand that warriors no longer have the niche they used to at the high end.  I say at the high end because in our little guild warriors are still kings for tanking the mobs we fight.   If I tried to tank Vindi the clerics would all go oom or I would just die very early on.<br>
<br>
SOE needs to find a way to make the warriors a viable class again, make no mistake - I know this and I agree.  All I am saying is that this Stand Down is a rediculous plan.  <br>
<br>
I also think it should be mentioned that nerfing the Pally's and SK's is not an answer.  I mention this because so many on the warrior boards seem to feel this is an acceptable course of action. (steel warrior anyway).<br>
