Apologies. No, that wasn't directed at you. That was the text at the bottom of the parse that I copy and pasted.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As for the HP and AC thing, well....maybe the Paladin and SK in question had more DKP than the warriors?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The equipment level of a Warrior to overtake a Paladin in HP, has to be higher than theirs. Or pretty damn close to it. Knights shouldn't be close to a Warriors HP, AC, or ability to tank high end content. Ever. They have their role and niche, we have ours.<br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Warriors innately have more HPs so I would think there would have to be a severe discrepency in AA's or gear for a Paladin to have more HPs. AC would have to be gear related as well so not an argument there either really<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Paladins have this spell <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3247&amp;source=Test" target="top">Aura of the Crusader</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> that stacks with your typical raid buff set up. This spell, right there, removes any HP advantage a Warrior can have due to higher STA returns (Which is the only advantage we have -- we do not innately just have more HP's. If we do, it is so minimal to the point of basically non existance.)<br>
<br>
Knights typically have more AC due to the fact they can use a shield unhindered. It is not practical for a Warrior to use a shield, as Furious Bash <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>still</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> does not work for our weapon procs. Warriors recieve no mitigation bonus, nor do they recieve any innate AC bonus.<br>
<br>
The reason that Knights have been able to catch up, (and overtake in some scenarios) is due to poor itemization in the high end zones. Any high HP/AC plate class item that slaps WAR/PAL/SK on it, moves Knights (statistically) closer to a Warrior. Raex (elemental armour) moved in the right direction, by making the Warrior class armour roughly 20% higher HP and AC. That's all forgotten when you enter Plane of Time, though, and you start to replace your elemental armour with WAR/PAL/SHD items.<br>
<br>
For a raid scenario, is there really any other way you can &quot;fix&quot; Warriors aside from nerfing Knights? If you increase our natural mitigation, grant us a HP or AC bonus, or play with our taunt, you seriously run the risk of trivializing EQ more than it already is.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is: We tank and taunt fine. Knights just do it too well. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21593&amp;alt=30620">Marshall Ainian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
