<br>
There's a sizeable increase in DPS vs undead, to be sure, and a visible one for non-undead.<br>
<br>
However, the time-equipped FT15 SK's are gonna be able to punch up the DPS at will far easier, and more often, than the Velious equipped SK's.  You guys have veiwpoints from two very distinct sphere's of EQ.<br>
<br>
From a development standpoint, I really doubt there is much SoE can do in this oft promised rebalance that won't negatively affect Knights.  As is the case far too often, the casual knight is going to feel this far more keenly than the end game knight.  The hew and cry of knights will surely be quite something.<br>
<br>
SoE pays the most attention to balancing against the end game.  A change that trivializes end game will allow progression far too easily and result in more people &quot;finishing&quot; EQ.  It's not in the best interest of the company to make the game too easy.<br>
<br>
As for &quot;demonstrations&quot;...  I think it's going to be a wasted effort.  SoE has already mentioned they will be making changes to melee.  Done wrongly, this would have a radical impact on the game.  It's no surprise it has taken this long.<br>
<br>
As for the Bulwark of Vie numbers, I think more empirical evidence is necessary, to rule out fluctuations due to randomness.  It's obvious that Knights are the currently preferred choice for exp groups, but, one test run won't *prove* (by numbers) that they make better boss mob tanks.  You'll need a wider sample set.<br>
<br>
I neither agree nor disagree with the assertion that Knight's take less DPS from boss mobs when using BoV.  I, however, won't be surprised is BoV works better for knights because of some unintended focus effect that should not apply.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kotos<br>
